    meaning: 'The Delayer',
    meaning_deep: 'The One who delays and postpones — whose timing is always perfect even when the delay causes suffering. Al-Mu\'akhkhir\'s delays are never negligence. They are wisdom operating at a level you cannot see from inside the waiting. The delay contains what the immediate answer could not have provided.',
    root: "''-KH-R · أخر",
    root_meaning: "To delay, to defer, to place after — Al-Mu'akhkhir controls the when of every event. His delay is always purposeful.",
    conditions: ['patience', 'fear', 'provision', 'wronged'],

    quran_reference: 'Surah Ibrahim 14:42',
    quran_verse: '"And never think that Allah is unaware of what the wrongdoers do. He only delays them for a Day when eyes will stare in horror."',
    quran_context: 'Al-Mu\'akhkhir\'s delay of the oppressor is specifically mentioned here — the delay is not abandonment of justice but its timing. Al-Mu\'akhkhir delays the punishment for a day when it will be complete and final.',

    prophetic_usage: 'The Prophet Yusuf waited 40 years. Prophet Ayyub waited years. Ibrahim waited decades for a child. In every case, Al-Mu\'akhkhir was at work — and the final delivery was always better than what the immediate answer would have been. The delay built what the answer then arrived into.',

