    dua_example: 'Ya Mu\'akhkhir, if what I am waiting for is delayed by Your wisdom, give me the patience to trust Your timing. Your delays contain what I cannot yet see.',

    significance: 'The scholars note that many of the greatest blessings in prophetic history came after the longest delays. The delay was the preparation — for the receiver, for the circumstances, for the impact. Yusuf\'s kingship required 40 years of preparation. Al-Mu\'akhkhir was building toward something.',

    reflection: 'If you received everything you asked for immediately, you would receive what you wanted at the moment you wanted it — which is not always what you needed, in the way you needed it, at the time that would serve you best. Al-Mu\'akhkhir delays for reasons that are perfect. The challenge is to trust that perfection while inside the wait.',
