    quran_context: 'This verse is considered one of the most comprehensive single verses about the nature of Allah in the Quran. Four names — First, Last, Manifest, Hidden — encompassing the complete range of existence in both time and space. He is before everything, after everything, manifest in everything, hidden beyond everything.',

    prophetic_usage: 'The Prophet ﷺ would say before sleeping: "Allahumma anta Al-Awwal fa laysa qablaka shay\', wa anta Al-Akhir fa laysa ba\'daka shay\', wa anta Az-Zahir fa laysa fawqaka shay\', wa anta Al-Batin fa laysa dunaka shay\'." The four names together as a prayer before sleep — a complete statement of reality.',

