    significance: 'The four names of Surah Al-Hadid 57:3 — Al-Awwal, Al-Akhir, Az-Zahir, Al-Batin — are called by the scholars the names that encompass all of existence. He is at every extreme of time (first and last) and every extreme of perception (manifest and hidden). Nothing is outside these four coordinates.',

    reflection: 'Before the Big Bang — before time and space existed — Al-Awwal was. After the universe ends, after time itself ends, after everything that has ever been ceases — Al-Akhir will be. The being who brackets all of existence at both ends is the One you are turning to in prayer.',
